cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.MM, cs.NE 

The paper deals with video processing and proposes a novel recurrent neural network architecture for temporal data. The focus is on action detection, which falls under computer vision (cs.CV). The paper also discusses optimization techniques and draws inspiration from classic theory on linear dynamic systems, which are topics related to machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). Additionally, the proposed architecture is evaluated on three challenging datasets, which are related to multimedia (cs.MM). Finally, the paper discusses the desirable properties of the proposed architecture, such as adaptively focusing computation and hierarchical decorrelation, which are related to neural networks (cs.NE).
